Senate Resolution 253
By: Senators Kennedy of the 18th, Jones II of the 22nd, Gooch of the 51st, Jackson of the
41st, Robertson of the 29th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing March 11, 2025, as Georgia Linemen Day; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Georgia's linemen are dedicated professionals who work tirelessly to ensure that
3 electrical power is restored to homes and communities during times of crisis, often under
4 dangerous and challenging conditions; and
5 WHEREAS, Georgia's linemen play an essential part in maintaining the state's power
6 infrastructure, ensuring the safety and well-being of Georgians before and after natural
7 disasters, storms, and other events; and
8 WHEREAS, during Hurricane Helene, a devastating hurricane that ravaged multiple areas
9 of Georgia, linemen were on the front lines, sometimes working up to 18-hour days in
10 hazardous conditions to restore power to thousands of residents in the wake of widespread
11 outages caused by downed power lines and infrastructure damage; and
12 WHEREAS, more than 8,000 women and men worked long hours in the aftermath of
13 Hurricane Helene, often in high winds and rain, demonstrating extraordinary courage,
14 resilience, and commitment to their communities as well as ensuring that power was restored
15 as quickly and safely as possible to support recovery efforts; and
