16 WHEREAS, the swift and efficient restoration of electrical services by Georgia's linemen
17 during and after Hurricane Helene was critical in enabling the recovery process, providing
18 relief to those affected by power outages, and ensuring the safety of residents and first
19 responders in the storm's aftermath; and
20 WHEREAS, Georgia's linemen continue to be instrumental in maintaining the state's
21 electrical infrastructure and responding to emergencies, including hurricanes and severe
22 storms, ensuring that Georgia's communities remain resilient in the face of natural disasters;
23 and
24 WHEREAS, our linemen's dedication to service exemplifies the values of hard work,
25 teamwork, and selflessness, making them unsung heroes during times of crisis; and
26 WHEREAS, it is fitting that the contributions of Georgia's linemen be recognized and
27 celebrated for their vital role in safeguarding the state's residents and infrastructure during
28 and after natural disasters, including Hurricane Helene.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
30 recognize March 11, 2025, as Georgia Linemen Day to honor and celebrate the exceptional
31 efforts of Georgia's linemen, past and present, in their ongoing commitment to public service
32 and the protection of our state's residents.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
34 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
35 press.
